bulario.reacoesAdversas:
➤ Severe peripheral and visceral vasoconstriction leading to ischemia or necrosis (especially in the fingers, toes, kidneys, and mesentery);
➤ Reflex bradycardia secondary to abrupt increases in systemic pressure;
➤ Ventricular arrhythmias including PVCs, VT, and rarely VF;
➤ Hypertension crisis, particularly with high-dose infusions or in volume-depleted patients;
➤ Headache, anxiety, tremor, pallor;
➤ Risk of metabolic acidosis in prolonged shock due to tissue hypoperfusion;
➤ Extravasation can cause local necrosis—requires prompt phentolamine infiltration.

bulario.reaccionesAdversas:
➤ Vasoconstricción excesiva con isquemia o necrosis periférica o visceral (dedos, riñones, intestinos);
➤ Bradicardia refleja secundaria a hipertensión abrupta;
➤ Arritmias ventriculares (TV, FV, extrasístoles);
➤ Crisis hipertensiva, cefalea, temblor, palidez, ansiedad;
➤ Acidosis metabólica por hipoperfusión sostenida;
➤ Extravasación puede causar necrosis—requiere infiltración con fentolamina.
